5000|$|The dental formula is: [...] The teeth often display {{signs of}} {{irregular}} development, with some teeth being exceptionally small, set at unusual angles or are absent altogether. <b>Honey</b> <b>badgers</b> of the subspecies signata {{have a second}} lower molar {{on the left side}} of their jaws, but not the right. Although it feeds predominantly on soft foods, the <b>honey</b> <b>badger's</b> cheek teeth are often extensively worn. The canine teeth are exceptionally short for carnivores. The tongue has sharp, backward-pointing papillae which assist it in processing tough foods.|$|R
