50|$|The {{endangered}} houbara bustard, {{a species}} of wader, breeds in the wild only at sites in the sanctuary. Other species found here include the largest wild population of the endangered Arabian gazelle, as well as Nubian ibex, Arabian wolves, <b>honey</b> <b>badgers,</b> and caracals.|$|R
50|$|The Jonkershoek Mountains, {{of which}} Stellenbosch Mountain is a peak, {{are home to}} Leopards, Caracals, Klipspringer, Baboons, <b>Honey</b> <b>Badgers</b> and Mongooses, however, all but the baboons are very secretive. Birdlife {{includes}} Kingfishers, Black Eagles, Fish Eagles, Spotted Eagle Owls, Sugarbirds, Orange-breasted Sunbirds and Protea Seed-eaters.|$|R
50|$|Otters are {{carnivorous}} mammals in the subfamily Lutrinae. The 13 extant otter {{species are}} all semiaquatic, aquatic or marine, with diets based on fish and invertebrates. Lutrinae is {{a branch of}} the weasel family Mustelidae, which also includes <b>badgers,</b> <b>honey</b> <b>badgers,</b> martens, minks, polecats, and wolverines.|$|R
